• Editor’s note: Livestream above courtesy DStv 403. You can also watch it on DStv Now. JOHANNESBURG - Members of the ANC are gathering in Limpopo ahead of the party's conference. The South Gauteng High Court is expected to rule on a case by disgruntled members on Saturday morning. The group wants the elective conference halted. WATCH: ANC Limpopo conference being served with court papers They say processes preceding this weekend's elective conference were unlawful. The group served the provincial leadership with court papers on Friday night. But the ANC says it's all systems go and anyone planning to go to court, should be in a position to prove they've exhausted all internal avenues. eNCA